              "identifier": "earl_warren",
              "name": "Earl Warren"
            },
            "byte_stop": 80081,
            "stop": 12.845,
            "byte_start": 28672,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "text": "Mr. Poulton, you may proceed.",
                "start": 0,
                "byte_stop": 80081,
                "byte_start": 28672,
                "stop": 12.845
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "start": 12.845,
            "speaker": {
              "last_name": "Poulton",
              "ID": 34987,
              "roles": null,
              "length_of_service": 0,
              "thumbnail": null,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/louis_p_poulton",
              "view_count": 0,
              "identifier": "louis_p_poulton",
              "name": "Louis P. Poulton"
            },
            "byte_stop": 2009799,
            "stop": 495.26,
            "byte_start": 80081,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "text": "Just before recess, I mentioned that the Machinists Union raises the defense of mootness if the Court should decide that this case is moot is not necessary for the Court to go into the second defense of the reliance upon the hot cargo clause in the Teamsters' contract.",
                "start": 12.845,
                "byte_stop": 157612,
                "byte_start": 80081,
                "stop": 32.209
              },
              {
                "text": "Now, as I pointed out prior to noon -- luncheon recess, on September 15th, 1954, the Machinists Union, which represented the production and maintenance employees of the American Iron and Machine Works Company, engaged in an economic dispute over the terms and conditions of the collective bargaining agreement with the employer.",
                "start": 32.209,
                "byte_stop": 254474,
                "byte_start": 157612,
                "stop": 56.446
              },
              {
                "text": "And as I said, during the strike, American Iron found it necessary to deliver its products to the common carrier's docks by means of its own vehicles.",
                "start": 56.446,
                "byte_stop": 301704,
                "byte_start": 254474,
                "stop": 68.238
              },
              {
                "text": "And the Machinists pickets follow these trucks and picket them in a u-shaped form at the common carrier's docks and only while they were at the docks.",
                "start": 68.238,
                "byte_stop": 345694,
                "byte_start": 301704,
                "stop": 79.242
              },
              {
                "text": "When the truck arrived, the pickets would picket and when the truck left, the pickets would leave.",
                "start": 79.242,
                "byte_stop": 374220,
                "byte_start": 345694,
                "stop": 86.383
              },
              {
                "text": "Now, due to this activity on the part of the Machinists, American Iron filed a charge with the regional director for the 16th Regional Board on September 24th, 1954 alleging a violation of Section 8 (b) (4) (A).",
                "start": 86.383,
                "byte_stop": 449348,
                "byte_start": 374220,
                "stop": 105.154
              },
              {
                "text": "Prior to the issuance of the complaint by the Board, the regional director petitioned the District Court of the Western District of Oklahoma seeking a temporary -- a preliminary injunction under Section 10 (l) of the Act.",
                "start": 105.154,
                "byte_stop": 514236,
                "byte_start": 449348,
                "stop": 121.373
              },
              {
                "text": "This petition was filed on October the 11th, 1954.",
                "start": 121.373,
                "byte_stop": 541508,
                "byte_start": 514236,
                "stop": 128.205
              },
              {
                "text": "The case was heard by Judge Wallace and it is known as Civil Case No. 6428 and is unrecorded.",
                "start": 128.205,
                "byte_stop": 572750,
                "byte_start": 541508,
                "stop": 136.006
              },
              {
                "text": "The case was tried and heard on October 16th, 1954, which time Judge Wallace dismissed the petition for the preliminary injunction.",
                "start": 136.006,
                "byte_stop": 623323,
                "byte_start": 572750,
                "stop": 148.652
              },
              {
                "text": "Now, on October the 21st, 1954, American Iron and the Machinists signed a collective bargaining agreement thereby settling the underlying dispute.",
                "start": 148.652,
                "byte_stop": 694063,
                "byte_start": 623323,
                "stop": 166.323
              },
              {
                "text": "This agreement contained a no-strike clause and was for the period of two years, all picketing by the Machinists ceased on October 21st, 1954.",
                "start": 166.323,
                "byte_stop": 757175,
                "byte_start": 694063,
                "stop": 182.108
              },
              {
                "text": "Now, two days after the underlying dispute was completely settled, the complaint was issued by the regional director.",
                "start": 182.108,
                "byte_stop": 817152,
                "byte_start": 757175,
                "stop": 197.102
              },
              {
                "text": "We contend that by issuing this complaint after the dispute had been settled, the regional director clearly abused his discretion since the controversy was rendered moot.",
                "start": 197.102,
                "byte_stop": 863336,
                "byte_start": 817152,
                "stop": 208.653
              },
              {
                "text": "Now, this Court -- first, let me say that the question of mootness is not raised in this Court for the first time.",
                "start": 208.653,
                "byte_stop": 906700,
                "byte_start": 863336,
                "stop": 219.501
              },
              {
                "text": "The question was originally raised before the trial examiner at the original hearing in the case.",
                "start": 219.501,
                "byte_stop": 936166,
                "byte_start": 906700,
                "stop": 226.851
              },
              {
                "text": "It was raised by way of a motion to dismiss on the grounds that the controversy was rendered moot.",
                "start": 226.851,
                "byte_stop": 963020,
                "byte_start": 936166,
                "stop": 233.584
              },
              {
                "text": "This motion was denied.",
                "start": 233.584,
                "byte_stop": 973991,
                "byte_start": 963020,
                "stop": 236.314
              },
              {
                "text": "It was again reinstated before the trial examiner and has been preserved all the way through to this Court.",
                "start": 236.314,
                "byte_stop": 1006174,
                "byte_start": 973991,
                "stop": 244.351
              },
              {
                "text": "The Court of -- the Board did not precisely rule on the question of mootness but rather accepted the trial examiner's intermediate report as to this aspect.",
                "start": 244.351,
                "byte_stop": 1070540,
                "byte_start": 1006174,
                "stop": 260.457
              },
              {
                "text": "Now, the trial examiner's intermediate report merely stated this and I'd like to quote from its record, page 31, “The undersigned finds that these developments, that was the signing of the contract, had not rendered the present proceeding moot, orders dealing with unfair labor practices have preventative as well as remedial purpose in effect.”",
                "start": 260.457,
                "byte_stop": 1169492,
                "byte_start": 1070540,
                "stop": 285.191
              },
              {
                "text": "The voluntary cessation of an unfair labor practice or private agreements for their end, do not deprive the Board of its power to add the sanction of a Board order and the possibly -- possible enforcement proceedings in order to bar any recurrence of those practices.",
                "start": 285.191,
                "byte_stop": 1259144,
                "byte_start": 1169492,
                "stop": 307.593
              },
              {
                "text": "The petitioner in 324, Machinists moved the Board, reconsider their decision and order on the grounds that the controversy was rendered moot and that they had not decided that issue.",
                "start": 307.593,
                "byte_stop": 1310239,
                "byte_start": 1259144,
                "stop": 320.38
              },
              {
                "text": "This was summarily denied.",
                "start": 320.38,
                "byte_stop": 1325181,
                "byte_start": 1310239,
                "stop": 324.114
              },
              {
                "text": "Now, this Court, in United States versus W. T. Grant Company, 345 U.S. 629 at page 633, stated in a question involving a violation of the Clayton Act whether that violation had been rendered moot, and I quote, “if the moving party must satisfy the Court, a relief is needed.”",
                "start": 324.114,
                "byte_stop": 1441583,
                "byte_start": 1325181,
                "stop": 353.212
              },
              {
                "text": "The necessary determination is that there exists some cognizable danger of recurrent violation, something more than the mere possibility which serves to keep the case alive.",
                "start": 353.212,
                "byte_stop": 1494350,
                "byte_start": 1441583,
                "stop": 366.417
              },
              {
                "text": "And we contend that there was no possibility of recurrence of the violation since the contract had settled the underlying dispute.",
                "start": 366.417,
                "byte_stop": 1547327,
                "byte_start": 1494350,
                "stop": 379.648
              },
              {
                "text": "And this Court in Local 74, the United Brotherhood of Carpenters & Joiners of America versus National Labor Relations Board, 341 U.S. 707 at page 715.",
                "start": 379.648,
                "byte_stop": 1611797,
                "byte_start": 1547327,
                "stop": 395.766
              },
              {
                "text": "Now this case, I'd like to go in the facts of this case, this case involved a secondary boycott by the Carpenters Union of a renovation project.",
                "start": 395.766,
                "byte_stop": 1646383,
                "byte_start": 1611797,
                "stop": 404.425
              },
              {
                "text": "Now, the renovation project was completed.",
                "start": 404.425,
                "byte_stop": 1666759,
                "byte_start": 1646383,
                "stop": 409.518
              },
              {
                "text": "Prior to that, there was a charge filed for by the -- I think it was the employer if I'm not mistaken because of a violation of Section 8 (b) (4) (A).",
                "start": 409.518,
                "byte_stop": 1704061,
                "byte_start": 1666759,
                "stop": 418.844
              },
              {
                "text": "Now, the carpenters raised the question of mootness whether the completion of the renovation project had rendered the controversy moot.",
                "start": 418.844,
                "byte_stop": 1742305,
                "byte_start": 1704061,
                "stop": 428.4
              },
              {
                "text": "This Court stated and I quote again, “This case has not become moot by the completion of the renovation project.”",
                "start": 428.4,
                "byte_stop": 1776368,
                "byte_start": 1742305,
                "stop": 436.923
              },
              {
                "text": "The complaint was against petitioners' use of secondary pressure upon Watsons, and that was the construction project in a manner prescribed by the statute.",
                "start": 436.923,
                "byte_stop": 1830076,
                "byte_start": 1776368,
                "stop": 450.33
              },
              {
                "text": "The use of such pressure on this renovation project was merely a sample of what might be repeated elsewhere if not prohibited.",
                "start": 450.33,
                "byte_stop": 1872917,
                "byte_start": 1830076,
                "stop": 461.054
              },
              {
                "text": "And the Court went on to say, the underlying dispute between petitioners and Watsons has not shown to have been resolved.",
                "start": 461.054,
                "byte_stop": 1916803,
                "byte_start": 1872917,
                "stop": 472.025
              },
              {
                "text": "Now in this case, we contend that the underlying dispute has been completely resolved.",
                "start": 472.025,
                "byte_stop": 1949926,
                "byte_start": 1916803,
                "stop": 480.292
              },
              {
                "text": "The dispute which gave rise to the picketing of Machinists was the economic strike over the terms of the contract.",
                "start": 480.292,
                "byte_stop": 1979079,
                "byte_start": 1949926,
                "stop": 487.599
              },
              {
                "text": "That dispute had been settled prior, prior to the issuance of the complaint.",
                "start": 487.599,
                "byte_stop": 1999976,
                "byte_start": 1979079,
                "stop": 492.813
              },
              {
                "text": "Now, the Board cites various cases --",
                "start": 492.813,
                "byte_stop": 2009799,
                "byte_start": 1999976,
                "stop": 495.26
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "start": 495.26,
            "speaker": {
              "last_name": "Warren",
              "ID": 15099,
              "roles": [
                {
                  "role_title": "Chief Justice of the United States",
                  "appointing_president": "Dwight D. Eisenhower",
                  "type": "scotus_justice",
                  "href": "https://api.oyez.org/preson_role/scotus_justice/2743",
                  "id": 2743,
                  "date_end": -16570800,
                  "date_start": -512503200,
                  "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States"
                }
              ],
              "length_of_service": 5740,
              "thumbnail": {
                "size": 50444,
