            },
            "byte_stop": 2025159,
            "stop": 499.118,
            "byte_start": 2009799,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "text": "Was the contract changed then, Mr. --",
                "start": 495.26,
                "byte_stop": 2025159,
                "byte_start": 2009799,
                "stop": 499.118
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "start": 499.118,
            "speaker": {
              "last_name": "Poulton",
              "ID": 34987,
              "roles": null,
              "length_of_service": 0,
              "thumbnail": null,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/louis_p_poulton",
              "view_count": 0,
              "identifier": "louis_p_poulton",
              "name": "Louis P. Poulton"
            },
            "byte_stop": 2047937,
            "stop": 504.795,
            "byte_start": 2025159,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "text": "Yes, sir.",
                "start": 499.118,
                "byte_stop": 2026726,
                "byte_start": 2025159,
                "stop": 499.498
              },
              {
                "text": "The contract was completely negotiated and was a new contract, sir, for a period of two years.",
                "start": 499.498,
                "byte_stop": 2047937,
                "byte_start": 2026726,
                "stop": 504.795
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "start": 504.795,
            "speaker": {
              "last_name": "Warren",
              "ID": 15099,
              "roles": [
                {
                  "role_title": "Chief Justice of the United States",
                  "appointing_president": "Dwight D. Eisenhower",
                  "type": "scotus_justice",
                  "href": "https://api.oyez.org/preson_role/scotus_justice/2743",
                  "id": 2743,
                  "date_end": -16570800,
                  "date_start": -512503200,
                  "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States"
                }
              ],
              "length_of_service": 5740,
              "thumbnail": {
                "size": 50444,
                "id": 32704,
                "href": "https://api.oyez.org/sites/default/files/images/people/earl_warren/earl_warren.thumb.png",
                "mime": "image/png"
              },
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/earl_warren",
              "view_count": 99,
              "identifier": "earl_warren",
              "name": "Earl Warren"
            },
            "byte_stop": 2065283,
            "stop": 509.152,
            "byte_start": 2047937,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "text": "Without that clause?",
                "start": 504.795,
                "byte_stop": 2056505,
                "byte_start": 2047937,
                "stop": 506.935
              },
              {
                "text": "Would that same clause --",
                "start": 506.935,
                "byte_stop": 2065283,
                "byte_start": 2056505,
                "stop": 509.152
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "start": 509.152,
            "speaker": {
              "last_name": "Poulton",
              "ID": 34987,
              "roles": null,
              "length_of_service": 0,
              "thumbnail": null,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/louis_p_poulton",
              "view_count": 0,
              "identifier": "louis_p_poulton",
              "name": "Louis P. Poulton"
            },
            "byte_stop": 2072074,
            "stop": 510.84,
            "byte_start": 2065283,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "text": "What clause were you referring to, sir?",
                "start": 509.152,
                "byte_stop": 2072074,
                "byte_start": 2065283,
                "stop": 510.84
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "start": 510.84,
            "speaker": {
              "last_name": "Warren",
              "ID": 15099,
              "roles": [
                {
                  "role_title": "Chief Justice of the United States",
                  "appointing_president": "Dwight D. Eisenhower",
                  "type": "scotus_justice",
                  "href": "https://api.oyez.org/preson_role/scotus_justice/2743",
                  "id": 2743,
                  "date_end": -16570800,
                  "date_start": -512503200,
                  "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States"
                }
              ],
              "length_of_service": 5740,
              "thumbnail": {
                "size": 50444,
                "id": 32704,
                "href": "https://api.oyez.org/sites/default/files/images/people/earl_warren/earl_warren.thumb.png",
                "mime": "image/png"
              },
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/earl_warren",
              "view_count": 99,
              "identifier": "earl_warren",
              "name": "Earl Warren"
            },
            "byte_stop": 2075941,
            "stop": 511.795,
            "byte_start": 2072074,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "text": "Well --",
                "start": 510.84,
                "byte_stop": 2075941,
                "byte_start": 2072074,
                "stop": 511.795
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "start": 511.795,
            "speaker": {
              "last_name": "Poulton",
              "ID": 34987,
              "roles": null,
              "length_of_service": 0,
              "thumbnail": null,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/louis_p_poulton",
              "view_count": 0,
              "identifier": "louis_p_poulton",
              "name": "Louis P. Poulton"
            },
            "byte_stop": 2079075,
            "stop": 512.586,
            "byte_start": 2075941,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "text": "The hot cargo clause, sir?",
                "start": 511.795,
                "byte_stop": 2079075,
                "byte_start": 2075941,
                "stop": 512.586
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "start": 512.586,
            "speaker": {
              "last_name": "Warren",
              "ID": 15099,
              "roles": [
                {
                  "role_title": "Chief Justice of the United States",
                  "appointing_president": "Dwight D. Eisenhower",
                  "type": "scotus_justice",
                  "href": "https://api.oyez.org/preson_role/scotus_justice/2743",
                  "id": 2743,
                  "date_end": -16570800,
                  "date_start": -512503200,
                  "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States"
                }
              ],
              "length_of_service": 5740,
              "thumbnail": {
                "size": 50444,
                "id": 32704,
                "href": "https://api.oyez.org/sites/default/files/images/people/earl_warren/earl_warren.thumb.png",
                "mime": "image/png"
              },
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/earl_warren",
              "view_count": 99,
              "identifier": "earl_warren",
              "name": "Earl Warren"
            },
            "byte_stop": 2085136,
            "stop": 514.107,
            "byte_start": 2079075,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "text": "Yes.",
                "start": 512.586,
                "byte_stop": 2085136,
                "byte_start": 2079075,
                "stop": 514.107
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "start": 514.107,
            "speaker": {
              "last_name": "Poulton",
              "ID": 34987,
              "roles": null,
              "length_of_service": 0,
              "thumbnail": null,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/louis_p_poulton",
              "view_count": 0,
              "identifier": "louis_p_poulton",
              "name": "Louis P. Poulton"
            },
            "byte_stop": 2121707,
            "stop": 523.251,
            "byte_start": 2085136,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "text": "Let me -- let me say this, Mr. Chief Justice, the hot cargo clause was not in the Machinists contract, sir.",
                "start": 514.107,
                "byte_stop": 2110004,
                "byte_start": 2085136,
                "stop": 520.318
              },
              {
                "text": "It was in the contract between the Teamsters and the common carriers.",
                "start": 520.318,
                "byte_stop": 2121707,
                "byte_start": 2110004,
                "stop": 523.251
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "start": 523.251,
            "speaker": {
              "last_name": "Warren",
              "ID": 15099,
              "roles": [
                {
                  "role_title": "Chief Justice of the United States",
                  "appointing_president": "Dwight D. Eisenhower",
                  "type": "scotus_justice",
                  "href": "https://api.oyez.org/preson_role/scotus_justice/2743",
                  "id": 2743,
                  "date_end": -16570800,
                  "date_start": -512503200,
                  "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States"
                }
              ],
              "length_of_service": 5740,
              "thumbnail": {
                "size": 50444,
                "id": 32704,
                "href": "https://api.oyez.org/sites/default/files/images/people/earl_warren/earl_warren.thumb.png",
                "mime": "image/png"
              },
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/earl_warren",
              "view_count": 99,
              "identifier": "earl_warren",
              "name": "Earl Warren"
            },
            "byte_stop": 2136022,
            "stop": 526.817,
            "byte_start": 2121707,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "text": "Yes.",
                "start": 523.251,
                "byte_stop": 2136022,
                "byte_start": 2121707,
                "stop": 526.817
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "start": 526.817,
            "speaker": {
              "last_name": "Poulton",
              "ID": 34987,
              "roles": null,
              "length_of_service": 0,
              "thumbnail": null,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/louis_p_poulton",
              "view_count": 0,
              "identifier": "louis_p_poulton",
              "name": "Louis P. Poulton"
            },
            "byte_stop": 2315536,
            "stop": 571.699,
            "byte_start": 2136022,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "text": "Now, the Board cites various cases to support its theory that this controversy was not rendered moot.",
                "start": 526.817,
                "byte_stop": 2162981,
                "byte_start": 2136022,
                "stop": 533.554
              },
              {
                "text": "I merely like to point out in the cases cited by the Board, there were no factual situations where the controversy had been rendered moot prior to the settlement -- have been rendered moot by a settlement of the underlying dispute prior to the issuance of the complaint.",
                "start": 533.554,
                "byte_stop": 2249812,
                "byte_start": 2162981,
                "stop": 555.26
              },
              {
                "text": "This case, we feel, falls into the dictum in the Carpenters case and we feel the Board and the General Counsel abused its discretion by issuing a complaint two days after the underlying dispute had been settled.",
                "start": 555.26,
                "byte_stop": 2315536,
                "byte_start": 2249812,
                "stop": 571.699
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "start": 571.699,
            "speaker": {
              "last_name": "Brennan",
              "ID": 15140,
              "roles": [
                {
                  "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                  "appointing_president": "Dwight D. Eisenhower",
                  "type": "scotus_justice",
                  "href": "https://api.oyez.org/preson_role/scotus_justice/2786",
                  "id": 2786,
                  "date_end": 648450000,
                  "date_start": -416862000,
                  "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States"
                }
              ],
              "length_of_service": 12330,
              "thumbnail": {
                "size": 56873,
                "id": 32778,
                "href": "https://api.oyez.org/sites/default/files/images/people/william_j_brennan_jr/william_j_brennan_jr.thumb.png",
                "mime": "image/png"
              },
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/william_j_brennan_jr",
              "view_count": 0,
              "identifier": "william_j_brennan_jr",
              "name": "William J. Brennan, Jr."
            },
            "byte_stop": 2331000,
            "stop": 575.578,
            "byte_start": 2315536,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "text": "Was the complaint -- was that complaint also against the Teamsters?",
                "start": 571.699,
                "byte_stop": 2331000,
                "byte_start": 2315536,
                "stop": 575.578
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "start": 575.578,
            "speaker": {
              "last_name": "Poulton",
              "ID": 34987,
              "roles": null,
              "length_of_service": 0,
              "thumbnail": null,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/louis_p_poulton",
              "view_count": 0,
              "identifier": "louis_p_poulton",
              "name": "Louis P. Poulton"
            },
            "byte_stop": 2335389,
            "stop": 576.669,
            "byte_start": 2331000,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "text": "Yes, sir.",
                "start": 575.578,
                "byte_stop": 2332463,
                "byte_start": 2331000,
                "stop": 575.922
              },
              {
                "text": "It was.",
                "start": 575.922,
                "byte_stop": 2335389,
                "byte_start": 2332463,
                "stop": 576.669
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "start": 576.669,
            "speaker": {
              "last_name": "Brennan",
              "ID": 15140,
              "roles": [
                {
                  "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                  "appointing_president": "Dwight D. Eisenhower",
                  "type": "scotus_justice",
                  "href": "https://api.oyez.org/preson_role/scotus_justice/2786",
                  "id": 2786,
                  "date_end": 648450000,
                  "date_start": -416862000,
                  "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States"
                }
              ],
              "length_of_service": 12330,
              "thumbnail": {
                "size": 56873,
                "id": 32778,
                "href": "https://api.oyez.org/sites/default/files/images/people/william_j_brennan_jr/william_j_brennan_jr.thumb.png",
                "mime": "image/png"
              },
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/william_j_brennan_jr",
              "view_count": 0,
              "identifier": "william_j_brennan_jr",
              "name": "William J. Brennan, Jr."
            },
            "byte_stop": 2350435,
            "stop": 580.422,
            "byte_start": 2335389,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "text": "Did -- did they join your mootness contention?",
                "start": 576.669,
                "byte_stop": 2350435,
                "byte_start": 2335389,
                "stop": 580.422
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "start": 580.422,
            "speaker": {
              "last_name": "Poulton",
              "ID": 34987,
              "roles": null,
              "length_of_service": 0,
              "thumbnail": null,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/louis_p_poulton",
              "view_count": 0,
              "identifier": "louis_p_poulton",
              "name": "Louis P. Poulton"
            },
            "byte_stop": 4177335,
            "stop": 1037.176,
            "byte_start": 2350435,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "text": "No, sir.",
                "start": 580.422,
                "byte_stop": 2351585,
                "byte_start": 2350435,
                "stop": 580.71
              },
              {
                "text": "They did not.",
                "start": 580.71,
                "byte_stop": 2364959,
                "byte_start": 2351585,
                "stop": 584.063
              },
              {
                "text": "I'd like to explain it if I may, sir.",
                "start": 584.063,
                "byte_stop": 2379379,
                "byte_start": 2364959,
                "stop": 587.654
              },
              {
                "text": "The contract between the Teamsters contains the hot cargo clause and that was what the violation, as I understand, Section 8 (b) (4) was predicated upon against the Teamsters.",
                "start": 587.654,
                "byte_stop": 2429430,
                "byte_start": 2379379,
                "stop": 600.175
              },
              {
                "text": "That dispute had not been settled.",
                "start": 600.175,
                "byte_stop": 2437266,
                "byte_start": 2429430,
                "stop": 602.146
              },
              {
                "text": "They still had that clause in their contracts, sir.",
                "start": 602.146,
                "byte_stop": 2448551,
                "byte_start": 2437266,
                "stop": 604.968
              },
              {
                "text": "Therefore, their case would not be rendered moot and they did not raise that contention.",
                "start": 604.968,
                "byte_stop": 2479167,
                "byte_start": 2448551,
                "stop": 612.614
              },
              {
                "text": "Now, I like to now turn to the hot cargo agreement, the Machinists reliance thereupon.",
                "start": 612.614,
                "byte_stop": 2539353,
                "byte_start": 2479167,
                "stop": 627.647
              },
              {
                "text": "We, of course, will adapt the Teamsters' position that the clause is legal and enforceable by direct inducement of the secondary employees.",
                "start": 627.647,
                "byte_stop": 2589717,
                "byte_start": 2539353,
                "stop": 640.258
              },
              {
                "text": "The courts below in the Rabouin case, Crowley Milk case, and in this case itself, found that the hot cargo clause removes the elements necessary to a finding of Section 8 (b) (4) (A) against the Teamsters.",
                "start": 640.258,
                "byte_stop": 2682295,
                "byte_start": 2589717,
                "stop": 663.404
              },
              {
                "text": "Now, if the clause itself removes the elements necessary to a finding of 8 (b) (4) (A), it removes the elements not only as to the Teamsters but as to whatever union is enthusing the secondary employees.",
                "start": 663.404,
                "byte_stop": 2782710,
                "byte_start": 2682295,
                "stop": 688.488
              },
              {
                "text": "There have been three courts at the present time that have considered the precise question of whether a union which is not a party to the contract containing hot cargo clause may use the hot cargo clause as a defense, one Court being the court below in this case which by a divided decision found that the clause was not available to the Machinists Union, although Judge Washington in a dissenting opinion in that case found that the clause was available as well to the Machinists as it was to the Teamsters.",
                "start": 688.488,
                "byte_stop": 2944564,
                "byte_start": 2782710,
                "stop": 728.957
              },
              {
                "text": "And he stated it made no difference as to who was doing the enthusing, whether it was the Teamsters or the Machinists.",
                "start": 728.957,
                "byte_stop": 2971209,
                "byte_start": 2944564,
                "stop": 735.615
              },
              {
                "text": "Now, also in this case in the 10 (l) proceedings, the same precise question was before Judge Wallace.",
                "start": 735.615,
                "byte_stop": 3006318,
                "byte_start": 2971209,
                "stop": 744.389
              },
              {
                "text": "Judge Wallace summarily, I might say, denied the petitions for injunction and therefore we contend that he also found or that he found that the hot cargo clause was available to the Machinists as a defense.",
                "start": 744.389,
                "byte_stop": 3078207,
                "byte_start": 3006318,
                "stop": 762.381
              },
              {
                "text": "Now, the third court which considered the contention was the District Court in United States District Court for Southern District of New York.",
                "start": 762.381,
                "byte_stop": 3151559,
                "byte_start": 3078207,
                "stop": 780.71
              },
              {
                "text": "In Dallas versus Teamsters, Local 707 in 1205, the district judge concluded that the hot cargo clause was not a defense as to a non-contracting union.",
                "start": 780.71,
                "byte_stop": 3222194,
                "byte_start": 3151559,
                "stop": 798.375
              },
              {
                "text": "He found it on the basis that the contracting union, pursuant to the actual language of the clause, reserves the right to apply the clause.",
                "start": 798.375,
                "byte_stop": 3271095,
                "byte_start": 3222194,
                "stop": 810.599
              },
              {
                "text": "The right was reserved.",
                "start": 810.599,
                "byte_stop": 3277573,
                "byte_start": 3271095,
                "stop": 812.222
              },
              {
                "text": "Therefore, he found that until the contracting union actually exercised its rights under the clause, it was not a defense to a non-contracting union.",
                "start": 812.222,
                "byte_stop": 3325848,
                "byte_start": 3277573,
                "stop": 824.274
              },
              {
                "text": "And when I say non-contracting union, I mean a union that is not a party to the hot cargo clause.",
                "start": 824.274,
                "byte_stop": 3353851,
                "byte_start": 3325848,
                "stop": 831.294
              },
              {
                "text": "Now, that case can clearly be distinguished and I think we can -- a petitioner in 324 can cite that as authority for our case in support of our contention that we can rely upon this hot cargo clause, since the clause in the present case says that the employees shall not be allowed, shall not be allowed to handle hot goods.",
                "start": 831.294,
                "byte_stop": 3461475,
                "byte_start": 3353851,
                "stop": 858.186
              },
              {
                "text": "There is no necessity on the part of the contracting union to exercise an option.",
                "start": 858.186,
                "byte_stop": 3485299,
                "byte_start": 3461475,
                "stop": 864.147
              },
              {
                "text": "There's no option given to them.",
                "start": 864.147,
                "byte_stop": 3494076,
                "byte_start": 3485299,
                "stop": 866.34
              },
              {
                "text": "So therefore, we contend that if the same factual report, the District Court, the same clause it would have decided that the handling of struck goods was removed from the course of the secondary employee's employment and the clause was available to a non-contracting union as a defense.",
                "start": 866.34,
                "byte_stop": 3591670,
                "byte_start": 3494076,
                "stop": 890.744
              },
              {
                "text": "Now, I'd like to point out something else that the Circuit Court in this case -- first I'd like to say this, I'd say the Board did not pass on this precise question of whether the defense was available to the Machinists because they found that the defense was not available to the Teamsters union therefore, automatically they found it wasn't available to the Machinists.",
                "start": 890.744,
                "byte_stop": 3695741,
                "byte_start": 3591670,
                "stop": 916.759
              },
              {
                "text": "The Circuit Court of Appeals, as I said by divided decision, found that the clause was not available and they found it on these grounds, that the Machinists union was neither the contracting union did not hold the contract containing hot cargo clause nor where we -- third-party beneficiary.",
                "start": 916.759,
                "byte_stop": 3810889,
                "byte_start": 3695741,
                "stop": 945.542
              },
              {
                "text": "Well, we will concede in any strict contractual sense we were neither -- we cannot deny that we were not the contracting party, but in a strict contractual sense, we were not a third-party beneficiary to the hot cargo clause.",
                "start": 945.542,
                "byte_stop": 3882047,
                "byte_start": 3810889,
                "stop": 963.33
              },
              {
                "text": "However, the clause was made for the benefit of another union other than the contracting union since the clause would be valueless to the contracting union.",
                "start": 963.33,
                "byte_stop": 3943173,
                "byte_start": 3882047,
                "stop": 978.609
              },
              {
                "text": "They would have no need for the clause.",
                "start": 978.609,
                "byte_stop": 3954563,
                "byte_start": 3943173,
                "stop": 981.462
              },
              {
                "text": "It was made for the sole purpose of helping either sister locals of the Teamsters or other labor unions that were caught in the throes of a strike.",
                "start": 981.462,
                "byte_stop": 4004927,
                "byte_start": 3954563,
                "stop": 994.062
              },
              {
                "text": "In summing up, I would like to say just this that first -- our first contention is the case was rendered moot prior to the issuance of the complaint and we think the Board and General Counsel abused its discretion by issuing the complaint because of the mootness.",
                "start": 994.062,
                "byte_stop": 4079950,
                "byte_start": 4004927,
                "stop": 1012.794
              },
              {
                "text": "And secondly, we would like to say that if the Teamsters conduct is permissive and the hot cargo clause is legal and enforceable by direct inducement of the secondary employees, then we feel that the clause is equally a defense to the Machinists contract.",
                "start": 1012.794,
                "byte_stop": 4168767,
                "byte_start": 4079950,
                "stop": 1035.006
              },
              {
                "text": "I thank you.",
                "start": 1035.006,
                "byte_stop": 4177335,
                "byte_start": 4168767,
                "stop": 1037.176
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "stop": 1037.176
      }
    ],
    "duration": 1037.176,
    "title": "Local 1976, United Brotherhood of Carpenters and Joiners of America, A.F.L. v. National Labor Relations Board"
  },
